<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="930" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d930">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6611.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Ciudad
                                    Juarez</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso, Texas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Reports from the south and west do not show conditions improving. Every
                            indication justifies the claim of the anti-Government faction and they
                            are daily growing in number. It is also becoming apparent that the
                            struggle now augmenting will prove to be a real war.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>